title: An Introduction to the Greek of the New Testament
creator: George Lovell Cary
description: LibriVox recording of An Introduction to the Greek of the New Testament, by George Lovell Cary. A collection of lessons (primarily in grammar) for New Testament Greek (also known as Koine) collected by a professor at Meadville Theological School of PA. There are over 80 short lessons, each covering an aspect of verbs, nouns, etc. (Summary by IWYLLPA) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
subject: librivox; audiobook; greek; language; vocabulary; grammar; instruction
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
